eventually recovered.

32:52.070 --> 32:56.908
Now Dr. Brantly and his wife,
Amber, have written a book about
the experience. He

32:56.908 --> 33:00.212
recently sat down with Hari
Sreenivasan in our New York
studio.

33:00.212 --> 33:04.549
HARI SREENIVASAN: So, it's
almost exactly a year ago, after
you quarantined yourself.

33:04.549 --> 33:10.856
You have got all the symptoms.
You have got the vomiting, the
diarrhea, the bloodshot

33:10.856 --> 33:15.460
eyes, things that you have been
seeing in patients and treating.
And, for the most

33:15.460 --> 33:19.064
part, those patients have been
dying. What's going through
your head?

33:19.064 --> 33:22.567
DR. KENT BRANTLY, Ebola
Survivor: Before I received my
diagnosis, the main symptoms

33:22.567 --> 33:29.074
I had were fever, fatigue,
body aches and diarrhea.

33:29.074 --> 33:36.181
When the diarrhea started, that
was more mounting evidence that
this really is probably Ebola.

33:36.181 --> 33:40.752
But I held on to that hope that
it was something else until we
had the definitive test result.

