DR. KENT BRANTLY: Nancy and I
actually talked on the phone. I
remember she called me and

34:03.742 --> 34:09.281
said, after we had the kind of
informed consent discussion with
the doctor that was in charge

34:09.281 --> 34:12.918
of our care, she said, "Kent,
what are you going to do?
Because I'll probably do
whatever

34:12.918 --> 34:15.787
you do."

34:15.787 --> 34:20.091
And I said, "I think I would
be willing to receive it."

34:20.091 --> 34:24.529
But it was -- you know, I
thought, otherwise, I'm probably
going to otherwise, and this

34:24.529 --> 34:30.769
may or may not help, but at
least I could be a guinea pig
and let the world know whether

34:30.769 --> 34:33.171
there is any benefit
to it or not.

34:33.171 --> 34:38.109
HARI SREENIVASAN: Once you get
this special air ambulance that
is arranged, the State

34:38.109 --> 34:41.513
Department, lots of people
working to try to make this
happen, it's a bit cloak and

34:41.513 --> 34:46.184
dagger. You're literally taken
to the airport at night.
There's -- before this, there

34:46.184 --> 34:48.920
are countries that don't even
want you flying over their
airspace.

34:48.920 --> 34:55.393
DR. KENT BRANTLY: It did seem
like something from a movie.

34:55.393 --> 34:59.364
When I got out of that, what we
called an ambulance -- it was
the back of a pickup truck

34:59.364 --> 35:05.670
-- and was being helped on to
the airplane, you know, I --
part of me really thought,

35:05.670 --> 35:09.407
this is pretty cool. I'm being
evacuated on like this
top-secret jet. And I wanted

35:09.407 --> 35:14.312
to look around and look at the
airplane, but it took every bit
of effort I had just to

35:14.312 --> 35:17.482
put one foot in front of the
other to get on to that
airplane.

35:17.482 --> 35:22.220
HARI SREENIVASAN: Let's talk a
little bit about your loved
ones. While you're in this

35:22.220 --> 35:26.458
kind of medically necessary
quarantine, your wife and your
kids were almost in a socially

35:26.458 --> 35:29.394
necessary quarantine of sorts.

35:29.394 --> 35:37.135
DR. KENT BRANTLY: They left
Liberia three days before I got
sick. And once my diagnosis

35:37.135 --> 35:44.709
was confirmed, they were put
in a quarantine of sorts.

35:44.709 --> 35:48.279
They were monitored by the
Health Department, had to check
their temperature several times

35:48.279 --> 35:54.319
a day, had to have two people
sign off on the temperatures
every day. But there was

35:54.319 --> 36:00.658
a lot of fear surrounding that
whole situation in the general
public. And people weren't

36:00.658 --> 36:06.231
sure what to make of a patient
with Ebola being brought back to
the United States, and

36:06.231 --> 36:09.000
then the recognition that, oh,
there other people who have been
in that country who are

36:09.000 --> 36:11.636
now walking around in public.

36:11.636 --> 36:15.507
And I think that created a lot
of fear because of the unknown.

36:15.507 --> 36:20.178
HARI SREENIVASAN: You also
mentioned that there were
certain cultural hurdles and
obstacles,

36:20.178 --> 36:22.647
that some of that fear was also
happening in West Africa in a
totally different way.

36:27.685 --> 36:30.288
Africa and here.

36:30.288 --> 36:34.692
Here, everybody was afraid that,
we're all going to get Ebola,
we're all going to die.

36:34.692 --> 36:43.835
In West Africa, the fear kind of
presented itself as denial that
Ebola was even real

36:43.835 --> 36:48.673
or that a loved one who had all
the symptoms of Ebola, but it
must be something else.

36:48.673 --> 36:52.043
HARI SREENIVASAN: What role do
you think your faith played in
all this?

36:52.043 --> 36:58.216
DR. KENT BRANTLY: That's a hard
question for me to answer,
because I try not to
compartmentalize

36:58.216 --> 37:04.189
my life into, this is my faith
life, this is my work life, this
is my family life.

37:04.189 --> 37:10.261
My faith is an integral part of
who I am. It's part of the lens
through which I view

37:10.261 --> 37:17.635
everything in life. So, I can't
separate this experience from my
faith.

37:17.635 --> 37:20.738
HARI SREENIVASAN: Some people
are going to say, look, the
difference might not be

37:20.738 --> 37:25.543
his faith. It's that he's an
American and he got literally
the best care on the planet

37:25.543 --> 37:28.913
for this, vs. all the people who
don't get that, not just in
Liberia, but anywhere else.

37:36.521 --> 37:42.227
I don't think there is anything
special about my faith that
saved my life. If anything,

37:42.227 --> 37:48.666
my faith is what put me in a
position where I got Ebola. And
I'm really thankful to

37:48.666 --> 37:54.806
the United States government, to
the government of Liberia, to
Emory University Hospital,

37:54.806 --> 37:59.577
to Phoenix Air, to the State
Department, all of the people
that played a role in providing

37:59.577 --> 38:03.681
me with the treatment
I received.

38:03.681 --> 38:08.720
I don't say that, oh, it was my
faith that saved me, not those
people. I believe God

38:08.720 --> 38:18.930
used those people to save my
life, not because of my great
faith. It just is. And so

38:18.930 --> 38:21.900
I give God the credit for it.
But I thank all of those people,
and I -- I love them.

38:22.734 --> 38:25.703
HARI SREENIVASAN: Would
you do this again?

38:25.703 --> 38:29.707
DR. KENT BRANTLY:
I would. I would.

38:29.707 --> 38:35.380
That is what Amber and I feel
like. That's the kind of life
God has called us to. And

38:35.380 --> 38:40.485
in some ways, we're really eager
to get back to that, to get out
of a life where we're

38:40.485 --> 38:44.856
doing book tours and stuff and
get back to the life of service
that we feel called to.

38:47.058 --> 38:49.427
The book is called
"Called for Life."

38:49.427 --> 38:51.596
Thanks so much for joining us.

38:51.596 --> 39:01.673
DR. KENT BRANTLY:
Thank you, Hari.

39:01.673 --> 39:07.879
GWEN IFILL: We will be back
with a conversation about how to
talk to your children about
religion.

39:14.619 --> 39:18.122
to ask for your support. And
that support helps keep programs
