39:20.558 --> 39:30.735
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now the latest
addition to the "NewsHour"
Bookshelf.

39:30.735 --> 39:36.741
Raising children is a journey
generously sprinkled with what
many view as teachable moments,

39:36.741 --> 39:40.712
perhaps none as challenging as
those surrounding faith and
religion.

39:40.712 --> 39:44.616
Author, journalist and
"NewsHour" online parenting
columnist Wendy Thomas Russell
comes at this

39:44.616 --> 39:50.622
from a different angle in her
new book, "Relax, It's Just God:
How and Why to Talk to Your

39:50.622 --> 39:53.591
Kids About Religion When
You're Not Religious."

39:53.591 --> 39:59.497
She recently talked with Jeffrey
Brown and explained how the book
came to be.

39:59.497 --> 40:04.802
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL, Author,
"Relax, It's Just God: How and
Why to Talk to Your Kids

40:04.802 --> 40:09.440
About Religion When You're Not
Religious": I was in the car,
and my daughter announced

40:09.440 --> 40:14.045
to me that God had made her and
that God had, in fact, made all
children and all people.

40:14.045 --> 40:14.679
And...

40:14.679 --> 40:17.515
JEFFREY BROWN: And you thought?

40:17.515 --> 40:22.487
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: And I was
so -- you know, she was so
incredulous because she just

40:22.487 --> 40:24.389
thought, this seems like really
big news, and how you don't know
it, mommy, is really

40:24.389 --> 40:25.823
beyond me.

40:25.823 --> 40:30.128
So -- but it did. It struck me.
I was really caught off guard by
it. And it...

40:30.128 --> 40:33.598
JEFFREY BROWN: And what
did you say to her?

40:33.598 --> 40:40.672
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: I didn't
say much at the time. I sort of
stumbled through

40:40.672 --> 40:43.975
the conversation, oh, who is
God? And I sort of stumbled
through the conversation,

40:43.975 --> 40:47.679
and then later went home
and talked to my husband.

40:47.679 --> 40:53.651
And he said, you know, it's not
what Maxine believes, but what
she does in life that matters.

40:53.651 --> 41:01.225
And it was a turning point for
me, this idea that, if we raise
kids to be moral and

41:01.225 --> 41:05.163
ethical and kind and generous,
then what they believe is
secondary. And it was -- it's

41:05.163 --> 41:07.865
been a guiding
force to the book.

41:07.865 --> 41:11.569
JEFFREY BROWN: I want to ask
you about the title. For so
many people, God and their

41:11.569 --> 41:13.805
religion are a basic component
of who they are. It's not just
God.

41:13.805 --> 41:15.606
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: Right.

41:15.606 --> 41:18.276
JEFFREY BROWN: And yet you use
that, just God, relax, it's just
God.

41:18.276 --> 41:19.477
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: Right.

41:19.477 --> 41:21.879
JEFFREY BROWN:
What do you mean?

41:21.879 --> 41:26.884
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: I don't
mean to be flippant or
insensitive in any way, but it

41:26.884 --> 41:32.023
does seem like there are certain
topics that are hard for parents
to talk about and to

41:32.023 --> 41:34.759
broach with their children.

41:34.759 --> 41:42.867
And, increasingly, religion is
becoming a one of them, and in a
lot of secular families,

41:42.867 --> 41:46.237
the word God is almost replacing
sex as kind of this taboo
subject. So...

41:46.237 --> 41:47.972
JEFFREY BROWN: The hard
discussion that parents might
have.

41:47.972 --> 41:50.141
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL:
Exactly. Yes.

41:50.141 --> 41:56.881
What I was getting at was that
it's not such a difficult
subject if you approach it in

41:56.881 --> 42:01.853
the right way. And so we
can all sort of lighten up.

42:01.853 --> 42:03.654
JEFFREY BROWN: You are coming
at this as a secular,
nonreligious parent.

42:03.654 --> 42:06.424
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: Correct.

42:06.424 --> 42:10.361
JEFFREY BROWN: You see a
growing need for this kind of
discussion.

42:10.361 --> 42:12.663
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: I do.

42:12.663 --> 42:16.901
Religion isn't going anywhere.
Religion is going to be around
for a very long time.

42:16.901 --> 42:21.839
But it's true that secularism is
on the rise. And it's growing
rapidly. And it's

42:21.839 --> 42:27.245
grown in the last 20 years. The
problem with a lot of parents in
this particular group

42:27.245 --> 42:33.551
is that they are trying to raise
their kids in this era of
transition or this era of
change.

42:33.551 --> 42:36.988
So let's come up with a way that
we can talk to our kids about
religion that's completely

42:38.923 --> 42:42.193
honest, that values critical
thinking, that values religious
tolerance and literacy, and

42:42.193 --> 42:46.731
that kind of leaves the door for
kids to really make up their own
minds.

42:46.731 --> 42:51.068
JEFFREY BROWN: Give me an
example of a common dilemma that
parents find when it comes to

42:51.068 --> 42:52.837
raising their children
vis-a-vis religion.

42:52.837 --> 42:56.507
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL:
There are quite a few.

42:56.507 --> 43:02.914
And I did a survey of 1,000
nonreligious parents to find out
exactly that. And the top
reason

43:02.914 --> 43:05.583
cited was, people weren't sure
how to talk about religion
without indoctrinating their

43:05.583 --> 43:08.519
kids into what they believed
themselves. That was a hard
line.

43:08.519 --> 43:11.889
The other one was interacting
with religious family members
and keeping the peace in
families.

43:11.889 --> 43:17.261
When you're raising a child who
is in a secular household, how
do you bridge the gap

43:17.261 --> 43:21.199
between the older generations
who may be more rigidly
religious?

43:21.199 --> 43:28.072
JEFFREY BROWN: This word
indoctrinating is an important
one, because it comes up time

43:28.072 --> 43:33.110
and time again here. What's the
difference between
indoctrinating and guiding
children,

43:33.110 --> 43:34.011
right?

43:34.011 --> 43:37.682
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: Right.

43:37.682 --> 43:52.096
Indoctrination, I see, as almost
the antithesis of critical
thinking. Of course it's fine

43:52.096 --> 43:55.967
to guide your children, but I
see indoctrination as sort of
this middle ground between
full-on

43:55.967 --> 43:59.704
brainwashing and guidance. it's
stronger than -- it's stronger
than just merely guidance.

43:59.704 --> 44:14.719
I see indoctrination as telling
children that there is only one
way to believe, and that

44:16.687 --> 44:28.599
all other ways and people who
believe all other things are
less worthy of our respect,

44:28.599 --> 44:37.975
less intelligent, less moral.
It's that -- that's the crucial
issue, because I think

44:37.975 --> 44:48.519
that, when you do that, you set
up your child to be bigoted
against those who don't believe

44:48.519 --> 44:51.756
the way that you do. You know,
we are -- it's not a
black-and-white world.

44:51.756 --> 44:56.127
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, so give me
an example of the most basic
question of -- your child

44:56.127 --> 45:01.666
says, mommy, does God exist and
what is God or who is God?

45:01.666 --> 45:09.140
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: The way
that I go about it is to say,
that's a great question,

45:09.140 --> 45:18.316
and I'm glad you're thinking
about it, that there are a lot
of different ways that people

45:18.316 --> 45:21.285
describe God and
describe what God is.

45:21.285 --> 45:31.896
And this is what some people
believe, and this is what other
people believe. And this

45:31.896 --> 45:37.735
is -- and I don't believe in
God, but that's OK. It's all
OK. And you get to make up

45:37.735 --> 45:40.871
your own mind about
what to believe.

45:40.871 --> 45:53.951
JEFFREY BROWN: Isn't that kind
of mushy? Isn't it the job of a
parent to guide -- I

45:53.951 --> 46:32.123
will use the word guide again --
their child to say, well, no,
it's not just this, it could

46:32.123 --> 46:39.897
be this, it could be that,
whatever you think, whatever
goes?

46:39.897 --> 46:42.533
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL: Right.

46:42.533 --> 46:48.439
Well, I think within reason.
And I do -- I see a difference
between guiding your child

46:48.439 --> 46:52.410
to be a moral person, an ethical
person, a self-respecting
person, a critical thinker.

46:52.410 --> 46:55.279
Those are all really
important things.

46:55.279 --> 47:17.034
Guiding them to believe in a
certain way, in a certain God or
a certain prophet, that

47:17.034 --> 47:56.340
is not so important. I really
want to focus on what people do
in life and not what they
believe, because if we can

47:56.340 --> 48:13.124
judge people on their actions,
and not what we think the
reasons behind their actions

48:13.124 --> 48:24.401
are, it makes for a more
tolerant world and a better
world.

48:24.401 --> 48:26.403
JEFFREY BROWN: All right.

48:26.403 --> 48:37.615
The book is "Relax,
It's Just God."

48:37.615 --> 48:44.155
Wendy Thomas Russell,
thank you so much.

48:44.155 --> 48:55.399
WENDY THOMAS RUSSELL:
Thank you, Jeff.

